nexml.^ot:comment: The tree in this study is based on the matrix from (this paper[http://www.biomedcentral.com/1471-2148/13/93]). There is a lot of missing data in this matrix. As such, there is a lot of uncertainty associated with this tree. We would suggest that analyses requiring a very precise estimate of topology collect additional data.
nexml.^ot:studyPublicationReference: Wright, April M., Kathleen M. Lyons, Matthew C. Brandley, David M. Hillis. 2015. Which came first: The lizard or the egg? Robustness in phylogenetic reconstruction of ancestral states. Journal of Experimental Zoology Part B: Molecular and Developmental Evolution 324 (6): 504-516
